race.comment: SOLAR ARC (4) has been flying this prep in easier races. Proved a shade too good last start over 1050m at Inverell. Lightly raced four-year-old who draws perfectly and has the services of Aaron Bullock so he is worth the gamble against this better opposition. WANAVAN (7) returned from a brief spell with a gutsy all-the-way win in a maiden over this distance at Muswellbrook last time out. Took a long while to get the monkey off the back but might go on with it now. OUTTA DE LADY (2) has been thereabouts in two runs this prep, both in BM66 sprints over shorter trips than this. At his best over five furlongs and back in a BM58 looks beautifully placed. DAO SUN (3) disappointed at Dubbo recently in a BM66 over this distance. Three-time winner at 1000m so don't rule him out coming back in grade. ROCK 'N' REIGN (6) wasn't far away at Dubbo last start and at the fourth run back with the shades reapplied he might be ready to produce.
